From 1042114b5853b238c47aacb9253f215595eb3dea Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SlayZone Dev <dev@slayzone.local>
Date: Sun, 19 Apr 2026 21:17:02 +0200
Subject: [slayzone] slayzone: Phase 8.2 processes webui +
 SlayzoneProcessesHost
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Second Phase 8 home-panel port. Read-only in 8.2 — lifecycle control
(start/stop/restart/delete) wires up alongside Phase 8.5 home-mode.

- chrome/browser/slayzone/mojom/processes.mojom: ProcessesHost with
  GetSnapshot() => (ProcessesSnapshot). Process struct captures label,
  command, cwd, status enum (string), pid, exit code, restart count,
  auto-restart flag, started-at.
- slayzone_processes_host.{h,cc}: per-SlayzoneBrowserView Mojo impl.
  GetSnapshot forwards to SidecarClient::Call(processes:get-snapshot).
  base::ListValue throughout (0022 hotfix).
- chrome/browser/ui/webui/slayzone/slayzone_processes_ui.{h,cc}:
  chrome://slayzone-processes/ WebUIController. Uses
  slayzone::ConfigureBundleSource helper.
- SlayzoneBrowserView: owns a SlayzoneProcessesHost; new
  processes_host() accessor.
- ChromeURLHosts() + webui_url_constants: register
  chrome://slayzone-processes/ host + URL constants.
- chrome_browser_interface_binders_webui_parts_desktop: registers
  ForWebUI<SlayzoneProcessesUI>().Add<ProcessesHost>().
- BUILD.gn: new .cc/.h files wired into browser + ui targets;
  mojom/BUILD.gn adds processes.mojom.
